column7: Industry Employment & Labor Force - by MONTH

column1: See notes at bottom of page for column definitions
NOTES: The unemployment rate is calculated using unrounded data. Data may not add due to rounding.
Note on column C:  County FIPS code or MSA designation
Note on column E:  the historical series has a non-economic break in January of years displayed.
Note on column F:  a '1' means the cell is currently estimated & published
a '2' means the cell is currently published but is determined by addition or subtraction
a '5' means the cell is currently published, is made up of multiple NAICS codes and is determined by addition or subtraction
Note on column G:  'SS-NAICS' refers to the North American Industry Classification System.
